President Biden has announced his nominees for key positions in his administration. Robert Godec is nominated for Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Kingdom of Thailand. Godec is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Senior Coordinator for Afghanistan in the Bureau of Population, Refugees, and Migration at the U.S. Department of State. He has previously held various positions, including U.S. Ambassador to Kenya and Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of African Affairs.

Vinay Singh is nominated for Chief Financial Officer at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. Singh is a Certified Public Accountant and currently serves as a Senior Advisor to the Administrator at the U.S. Small Business Administration. He has 25 years of private sector leadership experience, including as a Partner and Chief Operating Officer for the Infrastructure practice at KPMG in India.

Kalpana Kotagal is nominated for Commissioner on the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. She is a Partner at Cohen Milstein and specializes in civil rights and employment law. Kotagal is known for co-authoring the "Inclusion Rider," a legal template promoting diversity and inclusion in the entertainment industry. She has been recognized as an influential employment lawyer and is involved in various organizations focused on diversity and inclusion.

These nominees bring a wealth of experience and expertise to their respective positions and will play important roles in the Biden administration.